### 
Check List of vulnerabilities to look for during the engagement
##
1. Configuration Review
☐ Basic Server Configuration
   ☐ Server Fingerprinting
   ☐ Default Banner
   ☐ OPTIONS Header enabled
   ☐ TRACE Method enabled
   ☐ Default Error pages 
☐ Analyze request and response from app
☐ Sensitive information pages on server
☐ Check Directory listing
☐ Verbose Error Messages
☐ Default admin interfaces
☐ SSL Check
☐  Ip Address Leaks
☐ Proxy Present
☐ robots.txt
☐ Autocomplete Enabled
☐ Oracle Padding (check_patch.pl)

2. Application Study
☐ Analyze GET/POST/PUT/DELETE
☐ Check ObjectID, SessionID in GET request
☐ Replace methods (GET->  POST, POST->GET)
☐ Identify all Inputs 
   ☐ Search 
   ☐ Login 
   ☐ Register 
☐ Is CVV (Credit Card) sent in clear text
☐ Client Side Validation
☐ Critical Components
☐ Hidden Fields
☐ source Code Disclosure

3.  Authentication and Authorization
☐ Credentials sent in secure way
☐ User enumeration
☐ Password Control
☐ CAPTCHA present
☐ Password Remember
☐ Login after regisration
☐ Email activation required
☐ Concurrent login enabled
☐ Horizontal privilege checking
☐ Vertical privilege checking

4. Session management
☐ SessionID random-ness / prediction
☐ Session established methodology
☐ Cookie Settings
☐ Logout Functionality
☐ Session Timeout
☐ Session Fixation
☐ CSRF
☐ SessionID state
☐ Logout and cookie edit
☐ Caching issues

5. XSS
☐ Check output encoding
☐ XSS in url parameters
☐ XSS in input fields
☐ input validation
☐ input sanitization
☐ Server side Validation

6. SQL Injection
☐ Check for char blacklist
☐ Parameterized queries
☐ Different Encoding
☐ URL Encoding
☐ Base64 Encoding
☐ Blind SQL Injection
☐ Automated SQL Inkection

7. Other Injection Techniques
☐ LDAP Injection
☐ HTML Injection
☐ XML Injection
☐ XML Injection
☐ XPATH Injection
☐ HTTP Splitting
☐ CMD Injection
☐ CSRF Injection
☐ Char blacklist
☐ XXE

8. Other
☐ search Commands
☐ Parameter tampering
☐ Host Injection
☐ View State (.NET)
☐ URL Redirection (Open Redirect)
☐ Lockout users
☐ WebService testing (API)
☐ Email Enumeration
☐ JSON/JS Hijacking
☐ Content Caching enabled
☐ Spoofing/impersonating
☐ User of EVAL
☐ File Upload
☐ public information
☐ configuration file review
☐ encoder/decoder
☐ Local File Inclusion
☐ Remote File Inclusion
☐ SPF Missing FLag
☐ CORS
☐ SSRF
☐ CSRD
☐ Hostile subdomain Takeover
☐ ClickJacking
